trend_summary: Across the series, the landscape stays dominantly rural. Forest blocks contract slightly as rectangular crop fields expand, especially west of the central north-south ridge. Built-up footprints remain scattered, with only modest infill near the highway interchange. No large industrial or residential estates emerge; agriculture and woodland exchange area seasonally but pattern is stable.
notable_changes: Gradual enlargement of cultivated rectangular fields on the western plateau.
Minor forest clearing along the central ridgeline, reducing contiguous canopy.
Small cluster of new buildings and paved surfaces at the highway interchange.
Seasonal crop rotation visible as shifting field tones year to year.
Highway corridor and alignment remain constant with no major new roads.
